LISBON, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Following are some of the main stories in Portuguese newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

* Prosecutors shelve case on submarine purchases as no evidence of crime found, but say now deputy PM Paulo Portas exceeded mandate as defense minister in opaque deal (Publico) * Former head of BES Angola says bulk of 3.3 billion euros in BES financing of subsidiary never left Portugal (Sol) * Selling control of BFA bank is likely solution for Banco BPI's Angola exposure (Diario Economico)